# UI/UX Design Patterns

## Design System
- Use consistent spacing scale (4px, 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px, 48px)
- Implement consistent color palette for different states
- Use consistent typography scale and font weights
- Maintain consistent border radius and shadow values

## Component Patterns
- Create reusable components for common UI patterns
- Use compound component patterns for complex components
- Implement consistent loading states (skeletons, spinners)
- Use consistent error and success message patterns

## Layout Principles
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts
- Implement mobile-first responsive design
- Use consistent container max-widths and padding
- Maintain proper content hierarchy with headings

## Interactive Elements
- Implement consistent hover, focus, and active states
- Use proper cursor styles (pointer, not-allowed, etc.)
- Add loading states for all interactive elements
- Implement proper disabled states for forms and buttons

## Navigation Patterns
- Use consistent navigation structure across pages
- Implement breadcrumbs for deep navigation
- Use clear active states for navigation items
- Ensure keyboard navigation works properly

## Feedback & Notifications
- Use toast notifications for temporary feedback
- Implement proper success/error message patterns
- Use modals sparingly and with proper escape routes
- Provide clear confirmation for destructive actions

## Accessibility Standards
- Maintain color contrast ratios (WCAG AA compliance)
- Use semantic HTML elements appropriately
- Implement proper ARIA labels and descriptions
- Ensure keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Test with screen readers regularly

## Performance Considerations
- Lazy load images and heavy components
- Use proper image optimization (WebP, sizing)
- Implement virtual scrolling for large lists
- Minimize layout shifts with proper placeholder content
